# React Rules

- Use Functional Components only.
- Never use Class Components.
- Always use Hooks.
- Prefer Server Components where applicable.
- Use Client Components only when required.

## Components

- One component = one responsibility.
- Extract reusable UI.
- Keep components under 200 lines.
- Split large components.

## Props

- Always strongly type props.
- Prefer destructuring.
- Avoid unnecessary props.

## State

- Keep state local.
- Lift state only when necessary.
- Avoid prop drilling.
- Use Context only for truly global state.
- Use Zustand only if state becomes complex.

## Effects

- Avoid unnecessary `useEffect`.
- Never use `useEffect` for derived state.
- Always clean up effects.

## Keys

- Never use array index as key.

## Rendering

- Avoid nested ternaries.
- Extract render helpers.
- Keep JSX readable.

## Memoization

Only use `useMemo`, `useCallback`, and `React.memo` when profiling proves a benefit.

- Do not overuse memoization.

## Forms

- Controlled inputs.
- Strong typing.
- Validation.

## Accessibility

- Semantic HTML.
- ARIA only when necessary.
- Keyboard navigation.
- Visible focus states.
- 44px minimum touch targets.
